📌 1️⃣ Controller Layer – FinancialInstitutionController.java

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/common/financialInstitution")
public class FinancialInstitutionController {

    private final FinancialInstitutionService financialInstitutionService;
    private final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(FinancialInstitutionController.class);

    public FinancialInstitutionController(FinancialInstitutionService financialInstitutionService) {
        this.financialInstitutionService = financialInstitutionService;
    }

    /**
     * Endpoint for searching financial institutions.
     * Logs input parameters and result size.
     *
     * @param searchCondition The search parameters.
     * @return A list of matching financial institutions.
     */
    @PostMapping("/search")
    public ResponseEntity<List<FinancialInstitutionDTO>> searchFinancialInstitutions(
            @RequestBody FinancialInstitutionSearchConditionsDTO searchCondition) {

        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

        logger.info("[START] Searching financial institutions with criteria: {}", searchCondition);
        logger.debug("Received full request payload: {}", searchCondition);

        List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> results = financialInstitutionService.searchInstitutions(searchCondition);

        logger.debug("Raw service response before sending: {}", results);
        logger.info("[END] Search completed. Results found: {}, Processing time: {} ms", 
                results.size(), (System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime));

        return ResponseEntity.ok(results);
    }
}

✔ INFO logs request parameters (searchCondition) for visibility.
✔ DEBUG logs the entire request payload for debugging.
✔ INFO logs number of results and execution time.

📌 2️⃣ Service Layer – FinancialInstitutionServiceImpl.java

@Service
public class FinancialInstitutionServiceImpl implements FinancialInstitutionService {

    private final FinancialInstitutionRepository repository;
    private final FinancialInstitutionMapper mapper;
    private final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(FinancialInstitutionServiceImpl.class);

    public FinancialInstitutionServiceImpl(FinancialInstitutionRepository repository, FinancialInstitutionMapper mapper) {
        this.repository = repository;
        this.mapper = mapper;
    }

    /**
     * Searches for financial institutions based on provided criteria.
     *
     * @param searchCondition The search parameters.
     * @return A list of matching financial institutions.
     */
    @Override
    public List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> searchInstitutions(FinancialInstitutionSearchConditionsDTO searchCondition) {

        logger.info("Processing financial institution search with criteria: {}", searchCondition);
        logger.debug("Entering service layer with parameters: {}", searchCondition);

        List<FinancialInstitutionModel> institutions = repository.searchWithDynamicQuery(searchCondition);
        logger.debug("Repository returned {} records", institutions.size());

        List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> results = institutions.stream().map(mapper::toDTO).collect(Collectors.toList());

        logger.info("Search completed in service layer. Institutions found: {}", results.size());
        logger.debug("Mapped {} records from Model to DTO", results.size());

        return results;
    }
}

✔ INFO logs input search criteria for tracking.
✔ DEBUG logs entry/exit points and record count for debugging.

📌 3️⃣ Repository Layer – FinancialInstitutionRepository.java

@Repository
public class FinancialInstitutionRepository {

    @Autowired
    private CosmosClient cosmosClient;

    @Autowired
    private CosmosDBConfig cosmosProperties;

    private final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(FinancialInstitutionRepository.class);

    /**
     * Searches financial institutions dynamically based on provided criteria.
     *
     * @param searchConditions The search filters.
     * @return A list of matching financial institutions.
     */
    public List<FinancialInstitutionModel> searchWithDynamicQuery(FinancialInstitutionSearchConditionsDTO searchConditions) {
        
        logger.info("[QUERY START] Searching financial institutions");
        logger.debug("Received search conditions: {}", searchConditions);

        StringBuilder queryBuilder = new StringBuilder("SELECT * FROM FinancialInstitutions WHERE 1=1");
        List<SqlParameter> parameters = new ArrayList<>();

        if (StringUtils.hasText(searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionCode())) {
            queryBuilder.append(" AND financialInstitutionCode = @code");
            parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@code", searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionCode()));
            logger.debug("Added filter: financialInstitutionCode = {}", searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionCode());
        }

        if (StringUtils.hasText(searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode())) {
            queryBuilder.append(" AND financialInstitutionBranchCode = @branch");
            parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@branch", searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode()));
            logger.debug("Added filter: financialInstitutionBranchCode = {}", searchConditions.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode());
        }

        SqlQuerySpec querySpec = new SqlQuerySpec(queryBuilder.toString(), parameters);

        logger.info("[QUERY EXECUTE] Executing query: {}", queryBuilder.toString());
        long queryStartTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

        List<FinancialInstitutionModel> results = getContainer()
                .queryItems(querySpec, new CosmosQueryRequestOptions(), FinancialInstitutionModel.class)
                .stream()
                .collect(Collectors.toList());

        logger.info("[QUERY END] Query execution completed in {} ms. Results found: {}", 
                (System.currentTimeMillis() - queryStartTime), results.size());

        logger.debug("Raw database response: {}", results);
        return results;
    }
}

✔ INFO logs query execution and result count.
✔ DEBUG logs query-building process and raw database response.

📌 4️⃣ Global Exception Handling – GlobalExceptionHandler.java

@RestControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {

    private final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(GlobalExceptionHandler.class);

    /**
     * Handles validation errors (400 Bad Request).
     *
     * @param ex The validation exception.
     * @return ResponseEntity containing error details.
     */
    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleValidationException(MethodArgumentNotValidException ex) {
        
        logger.info("Validation error occurred: {}", ex.getMessage());
        logger.debug("Full validation error details: {}", ex.getBindingResult().getAllErrors());

        ErrorResponseDTO errorResponse = new ErrorResponseDTO("400", "Invalid parameter value", 
                null, LocalDateTime.now(), null);

        return new ResponseEntity<>(errorResponse, HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST);
    }

    /**
     * Handles general exceptions (500 Internal Server Error).
     *
     * @param ex The unexpected exception.
     * @return ResponseEntity containing error details.
     */
    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponseDTO> handleGeneralException(Exception ex) {
        
        logger.error("Unexpected error occurred: {}", ex.getMessage());
        logger.debug("Exception stack trace: ", ex);

        ErrorResponseDTO errorResponse = new ErrorResponseDTO("500", "An unexpected error occurred", 
                null, LocalDateTime.now(), null);

        return new ResponseEntity<>(errorResponse, HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
    }
}
✅ How INFO and DEBUG Will Log searchCondition Differently?

By default, both INFO and DEBUG logs will print the same format if searchCondition is passed directly. However, if we want:
	•	INFO to log a concise key-value format
	•	DEBUG to log a full JSON structure

We need custom formatting.

📌 Solution: Format INFO and DEBUG Logs Differently

Modify the logging statements so that INFO logs a simple key-value format, while DEBUG logs the full JSON payload.

🔹 Updated Controller Logging

@PostMapping("/search")
public ResponseEntity<List<FinancialInstitutionDTO>> searchFinancialInstitutions(
        @RequestBody FinancialInstitutionSearchConditionsDTO searchCondition) {

    long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();

    // INFO: Log search condition in key-value format
    logger.info("[START] Searching financial institutions with criteria: {}", formatForInfoLog(searchCondition));

    // DEBUG: Log full JSON structure
    logger.debug("Received full request payload: {}", convertToJson(searchCondition));

    List<FinancialInstitutionDTO> results = financialInstitutionService.searchInstitutions(searchCondition);

    logger.debug("Raw service response before sending: {}", convertToJson(results));
    logger.info("[END] Search completed. Results found: {}, Processing time: {} ms", 
            results.size(), (System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime));

    return ResponseEntity.ok(results);
}

✔ INFO logs key-value format
✔ DEBUG logs full JSON payload

📌 Implement Formatting Methods

🔹 1️⃣ Convert to Key-Value Format for INFO Logs

private String formatForInfoLog(FinancialInstitutionSearchConditionsDTO searchCondition) {
    return String.format("financialInstitutionCode=%s, branchCode=%s, name=%s",
            searchCondition.getFinancialInstitutionCode(),
            searchCondition.getFinancialInstitutionBranchCode(),
            searchCondition.getName());
}

✔ Creates a compact key-value format for INFO logs.
✔ Prints something like:

[INFO] Searching financial institutions with criteria: financialInstitutionCode=123, branchCode=null, name=XYZ Bank

🔹 2️⃣ Convert to JSON for DEBUG Logs

private String convertToJson(Object object) {
    try {
        return new ObjectMapper().writeValueAsString(object);
    } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {
        return "Error converting to JSON: " + e.getMessage();
    }
}

✔ Converts any Java object to a JSON string for DEBUG logs.
✔ Prints something like:

[DEBUG] Received full request payload: {"financialInstitutionCode":"123","branchCode":null,"name":"XYZ Bank"}

